article:
The Melbourne Cup is Australia's major Thoroughbred horse race. Each year
internationally bred or owned horses compete in the race. Since 1882 New Zealand
bred horses have won 40 Melbourne Cups, British bred horses have won five cups,
US bred horses four, Irish horses two and Japanese bred horses one Melbourne Cup
in 2006. [http://www.studbook.org.au/RaceWinnersHistory.aspx?RACEID=4001 ASB
VRC Melbourne Cup Race Winners] Retrieved on 2009-7-25

This is a list of the winners of the Melbourne Cup, a Thoroughbred horse race at
Flemington Racecourse in Melbourne, Australia.
